## Overview

Dropdown is a single-select combobox: a labelled Field trigger that opens a menu of options. It exposes three Figma variant axes — Validation (Default / Success / Error), State (Default / Hover / Focus / Disabled), and Content (Empty / Selected Option / Placeholder Text) — plus boolean toggles for the optional Label, helper text, error text, requirement markers, scrolling menu, and the open/closed menu. The Field resolves its displayed text by priority (selected value, else placeholder, else empty), and validation drives the field border, validation icon, and helper/error messaging. Colour is token-bound across 18 semantic tokens with no mode collection; structure is fully measured for the default size with per-state and per-validation deltas documented separately.

**Variant axes.** **Validation** (Default / Success / Error; default Default); **State** (Default / Hover / Focus / Disabled; default Default); **Content** (Empty / Selected Option / Placeholder Text; default Empty).

