## API

_Confidence: medium — 1 sub-component(s) unresolved; see Known gaps._

> The Field affordance resolves its displayed content by priority: when value is set the selected option label renders; else when placeholder is set the placeholder renders; else the field is empty. The 'Content' Figma axis (Empty / Selected Option / Placeholder Text) is the visual projection of this value+placeholder state and is not a runtime prop. The 'requirement' enum is mutually exclusive: a field is either required (shows the '*' marker, aria-required=true) or optional (shows the '(optional)' tag) or neither — never both, so the two Figma booleans isRequired and isOptional are merged. isMenuOpen controls whether the option Menu overlay is rendered; hasScrollingMenu (and its scroll bar) only renders meaningfully when isMenuOpen=true. When isDisabled=true the whole control is non-interactive and aria-disabled=true is exposed.

| Property | Type | Values | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `validationState` | variant | default \| success \| error | default | Validation styling and messaging. Figma axis 'Validation'. error pairs with errorText; success is a confirmation treatment. |
| `isDisabled` | boolean | true \| false | false | Persistent disabled state. Decomposed from the Figma 'State' axis (Hover and Focus are transient runtime states and are not API props). Exposes aria-disabled=true. |
| `isMenuOpen` | boolean | true \| false | false | Whether the options Menu overlay is shown. Figma boolean 'isMenuOpen'. Drives aria-expanded. |
| `value` | text | (string) | – | Selected option label shown in the Field. When set, renders the 'Selected Option' content state. Figma editable text '↪ Input'. |
| `placeholder` | text | (string) | – | Placeholder text shown in the Field when no value is selected. Renders the 'Placeholder Text' content state. Figma editable text '↪ Placeholder'. |
| `hasLabel` | boolean | true \| false | true | Whether the Label container renders. Figma boolean 'hasLabel'. |
| `label` | text | (string) | "Label" | Field label text. Figma editable text '↪ Label'. Only visible when hasLabel=true. |
| `requirement` | variant | none \| required \| optional | none | Mutually-exclusive label affordance merged from Figma booleans isRequired ('*' marker) and isOptional ('(optional)' tag). required also exposes aria-required=true. Off-state is none. |
| `hasHelperText` | boolean | true \| false | true | Whether the Helper text container renders below the Field. Figma boolean 'hasHelperText'. |
| `helperText` | text | (string) | "Helper text" | Supporting text below the Field. Figma editable text '↪ Helper Text'. Only visible when hasHelperText=true. |
| `hasErrorText` | boolean | true \| false | true | Whether the Error text container renders. Figma boolean 'hasErrorText'. Typically paired with validationState=error. |
| `errorText` | text | (string) | "Error text" | Validation error message. Figma editable text '↪ Error Text'. Only visible when hasErrorText=true. |
| `hasScrollingMenu` | boolean | true \| false | true | Whether the open Menu shows a scroll bar for overflowing options. Figma boolean 'hasScrollingMenu'. Only meaningful when isMenuOpen=true. |

