### Example 1 — Default closed dropdown with placeholder

```pseudocode
Dropdown(
  label: "Country",
  placeholder: "Select a country",
  helperText: "Choose your country of residence",
  validationState: default,
)
```

_Text overrides:_ Label = "Country"; Placeholder = "Select a country"; Helper text = "Choose your country of residence"

### Example 2 — Open menu with selected value

```pseudocode
Dropdown(
  value: "United Kingdom",
  isMenuOpen: true,
  hasScrollingMenu: true,
)
```

_Text overrides:_ Label = "Country"; Input = "United Kingdom"

### Example 3 — Required field in error

```pseudocode
Dropdown(
  validationState: error,
  requirement: required,
  errorText: "Please select a country",
  hasErrorText: true,
)
```

_Text overrides:_ Label = "Country"; Error text = "Please select a country"

### Example 4 — Disabled optional dropdown

```pseudocode
Dropdown(
  isDisabled: true,
  requirement: optional,
  placeholder: "Select a region",
)
```

_Text overrides:_ Label = "Region"; Placeholder = "Select a region"

