## Structure

_Confidence: high._ _Reconciliation: 0 auto-fixed, 0 retried, 1 unresolved._

> Dropdown has no size or density axis — its three Figma variant axes are Validation (Default/Success/Error), State (Default/Hover/Focus/Disabled), and Content (Empty/Selected Option/Placeholder Text). Validation and State are predominantly color/visual axes; the only dimensional/structural deltas are: (1) the field border weight, which thickens on Hover (bottom edge -> 2) and Focus (all edges -> 2) — see Dropdown — Focus & Hover; (2) the Error validation state, which inserts an Error text container and a 4 left accent border (Error border) — see Dropdown — Error. Content is structural in the narrow sense that it swaps which text child renders in the Field (Value vs Placeholder vs none) with no dimensional change — captured in visualOnlyAxisDeltas. Many container frames carry strokeWeight=1 as a default property with no painted stroke (Label container, Field icon, Helper text container, Optional tag, Menu container, Scroll bar, Error text container, Error icon); per the structure-spec border gate these are not borders and emit no borderWidth row. Only the Field (#666666), the Menu (#bdbdbd, bottom/start/end only), and the Error border (4 start accent) paint actual strokes. Menu options are .Menu item library instances (boundary — internals deferred to the Menu item spec). Spacing tokens split between two families: spacing/fixed/* (label, helper, menu, error insets) and spacing/fluid/* (field insets) — the field uses fluid tokens so its inset can flex with layout, while structural gaps use fixed tokens.

