### Dropdown — Focus & Hover

Interaction states thicken the field border for affordance. Hover thickens only the bottom edge to 2; Focus thickens the whole border uniformly to 2. Default and Disabled keep the uniform 1 border. Dimensions are otherwise identical across states.

| Spec | Default | Hover | Focus | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Field | – | – | – | Only the field border weight changes between these states |
| borderWidth | 1 | 1 / 2 | 2 | Hover thickens the bottom edge only (top/start/end stay 1); Focus thickens all edges to 2 |
| borderAlign | inside | inside | inside | Stroke stays inside the field bounds in all states |

