_Confidence: high._

> Dropdown is a single-select combobox: the Field is the trigger that opens a popup listbox of Menu items. The visible Label, the Required marker ("*") / Optional tag ("(optional)"), the selected Value or placeholder, and the Helper text all merge into the Field's announcement - they are not separate focus stops. The chevron icon and the Scroll bar / Scroll thumb are decorative. Error text is a live region surfaced as the Field's error description, not a focus stop. Focus order has two stops: (1) the Field/combobox trigger, always present; (2) each Menu item, reachable only while the menu is open - on web the listbox uses active-descendant so DOM focus stays on the combobox, while iOS and Android move focus into the option rows. Do not reorder focus across states; keep the Field at stop 1 so the open/close gesture stays predictable. Do not stuff the accessible name with the helper text, value, and error - each belongs on its own property (value, hint, and invalid/error description). Platform parity note: web keeps the combobox as the single DOM focus stop and exposes options via aria-activedescendant; iOS VoiceOver and Android TalkBack move focus onto each option - the focusOrder documents the superset (combobox + option). When disabled, the Field is removed from the focus order entirely and exposes a disabled state only.

### Focus order

Label, Required marker / Optional tag, the selected Value or placeholder, and Helper text all merge into the Field's announcement. The Field is the only stop while the menu is closed. When the menu is open, each Menu item becomes a reachable option (web via aria-activedescendant on the combobox; iOS/TalkBack move focus into the rows).

| # | Part | Announcement | Role | Properties | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Field | "Label, [selected value or placeholder], combo box, Helper text" | combobox / popup button | Merged parts: Label, Required marker, Optional tag, Value/placeholder, Helper text; Has popup: listbox | — |
| 2 | Menu item | "Option, X of N" | option (within listbox) | Availability: Menu open only; Position: X of N | — |

### State: enabled (closed)

Default / Hover / Focus collapsed dropdown with a selected value or placeholder. Hover and Focus are transient, platform-handled, and identical to Default for screen readers, so they are grouped here.

#### VoiceOver (iOS)

| Property | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Announcement | "Country, United Kingdom, button, Choose a country" | |
| accessibilityLabel | "Country" | From the visible Label (merged) - the accessible name of the trigger. |
| accessibilityValue | "United Kingdom" | The selected Value; when empty, the placeholder text is read instead. |
| accessibilityTraits | .isButton | The collapsed Field acts as a popup button that opens the option list. |
| accessibilityHint | "Choose a country" | From the Helper text (merged) - describes the result, not the gesture. |
| Do NOT | expose Label as a separate element | The Label merges into the Field's name; do not read it twice or list it as its own focus stop. |
| Do NOT | announce the chevron icon | Decorative - mark accessibilityElementsHidden = true so it is not read. |
| Do NOT | expose Helper text as a separate stop | It is the Field's accessibilityHint, not an independent focus stop. |

#### TalkBack (Android)

| Property | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Announcement | "Country, United Kingdom, drop-down list, double-tap to activate, Choose a country" | |
| contentDescription | "Country" | From the visible Label (merged via mergeDescendants). |
| stateDescription | "United Kingdom" | The selected Value; placeholder text when no value is selected. |
| role | Role.DropdownList | The collapsed Field is a drop-down list trigger. |
| Hint | "Choose a country" | From the Helper text (merged) - spoken after the role. |
| Do NOT | read the Label twice | It merges into contentDescription; do not expose the Label node as a separate focusable element. |
| Do NOT | announce the chevron icon | Decorative - set importantForAccessibility = no on the chevron and the Scroll bar. |

#### ARIA (Web)

| Property | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Announcement | "Country, United Kingdom, combo box, collapsed, Choose a country" | |
| role | combobox | Field is a combobox trigger; prefer a native <select> or a button with role="combobox". |
| aria-labelledby | label-id | Associates the visible Label with the combobox instead of duplicating it via aria-label. |
| aria-expanded | false | Collapsed state - the popup listbox is not shown. |
| aria-haspopup | listbox | Indicates the control opens a listbox of options. |
| aria-describedby | helper-id | Associates the Helper text as the field's description. |
| Do NOT | duplicate the Label as aria-label | A visible Label exists; reference it via aria-labelledby - the visible label wins. |
| Do NOT | expose the chevron or Scroll bar | Decorative - mark aria-hidden = true. |

