| Announcement | "Country, United Kingdom, button, invalid data, Please select a country" | |
| accessibilityLabel | "Country" | Unchanged from the enabled state. |
| accessibilityValue | "United Kingdom, invalid data" | Folds the invalid state into the value rather than a standalone glyph. |
| accessibilityHint | "Please select a country" | Error text replaces the Helper text as the field's description. |
| Live region | post an accessibility notification on error | Error text appears reactively - announce it without making it a focus stop. |
| Do NOT | announce the error glyph as a standalone element | Fold the indicator into the Field's value / hint, not a separate focusable node. |

#### TalkBack (Android)

| Property | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Announcement | "Country, United Kingdom, drop-down list, error, Please select a country" | |
| contentDescription | "Country" | Unchanged from the enabled state. |
| error | error("Please select a country") | Sets the field's error semantics from the Error text. |
| liveRegion | LiveRegionMode.Polite | Error text container announces politely when it appears. |
| Do NOT | announce the error glyph standalone | Fold it into the field's error() state, not a separate element. |

